aVIt turns out that in addition to the assumed reasons,
p72
aVpay secrecy is actually a way to save a lot of money.
p73
aVYou see, keeping salaries secret
p74
aVleads to what economists call "information asymmetry."
p75
aVThis is a situation where, in a negotiation,
p76
aVone party has loads more information than the other.
p77
aVAnd in hiring or promotion or annual raise discussions,
p78
aVan employer can use that secrecy to save a lot of money.
p79
aVImagine how much better you could negotiate for a raise
p80
aVif you knew everybody's salary.
