VEconomists warn that information asymmetry
p83
aVcan cause markets to go awry.
p84
aVSomeone leaves a pay stub on the copier,
p85
aVand suddenly everybody is shouting at each other.
p86
aVIn fact, they even warn
p87
aVthat information asymmetry can lead to a total market failure.
